nmap -sCV -p- <IP> --> Service, Script + all ports
nmap --script safe <IP> --> Hidden Services, Weak Configs, Extra service info
nmap --script vuln <IP> --> Vulnerability Scan
nmap -sS -sV --version-intensity 9 <IP> --> Deep Probing/Firewall for Obfuscation/hidden/masked services
nmap --script banner <IP> --> reveals hidden services
nmap -sS -Pn -T1 -f --data-length 200 --randomize-hosts <IP> --> Remove -Pn to remove bypass ping/ICMP block

Save as much data as needed into files so you can revisit later (very useful) 
-oN/-oX/-oS/-oG <file>: Output scan in normal, XML, s|<rIpt kIddi3, and Grepable format, respectively, to the given filename.
